ight'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.3pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">To inform this review it agreed that individual </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">committees should be invited to submit a memorandum to the Liaison Committee by 30 October 2013 setting out:</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">how they have responded to the Committee’s best practice recommendations</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">how they have approached the revised core tasks approved by the House in </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">January 2012</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">any obstacles encountered</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">any examples of innovation or good practice for others to consider.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.3pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">The Administration Committee is a domestic select committee rather than a departmental one. This means that many of the core tasks (such as scrutiny</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt"> of draft bills, major public appointments and government departmental finances and policies) are not relevant. However, there are recommendations where the Administration Committee has made progress and this is worth reporting to the Liaison Committee. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Recommendation 24</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.3pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">As a model of ‘best practice’, we recommend that committees:</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.22pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Clearly record their conclusions and remind themselves of them when considering proposals for inquiry and programme planning</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.22pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Canvass opinion among the key player</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">s</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> in their subject area about their performance.</span></li></ul></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">When revisiting a topic, previous recommendations and minutes are always referred to in order to remind the Committee of its original view and the circumstances which led to that opinion. This is especially </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">important when there is a high turnover of members</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">resulting in a short-term collective memory. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">The Chair, via the Clerk, regularly seeks informal feedback from the House Service about the performance of the Committee and how it could get the best out of</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt"> witnesses. Likewise, the views of members have been sought about what is needed from witnesses to make meetings more effective. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Recommendation 33</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.3pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">We encourage committees to keep their reports shorts and accessible, and to avoid too many recommendations. A clear indication </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">of which recommendations </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">are most important will help the committee achieve the impact and make follow-up easier. [...] We sugges</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">t that conclusions should be in bold, with recommendations </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">in bold italics, and that it should be clearly stated to whom the recommendation is addressed.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">The Committee has only </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">produced</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt"> one report since the Liaison Committee </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">made</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt"> its recommendations. Howe</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">ver, that </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">report (</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">First weeks at Westminster; induction arrangements for new MPs in 2015, </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">HC 193, 2013-14) was shorter than previous reports at 100 paragraphs long and did put conclusions in bold and recommendations in bold italics.  The recommendations cl</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">early identified who was expected to deliver the recommendation and where possible a timeframe for delivery. (The Committee finds the mnemonic ‘S.M.A.R.T.’ useful when considering the wording of recommendations to ensure that they are </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">s</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">pecific, </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">m</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">easurable,</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">a</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">chievable, </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">r</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">ealistic and </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">t</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">ime-bound).</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">For example:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">“We recommend that PICT consults this Committee by May 2014 on the detailed mechanics of how the post-2015 scheme for providing IT equipment to Members would work in practice”. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">              </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Recommendation 34</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.3pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">We recommend that each committee should appoint a member of staff, or an adviser, or an outside body who will monitor follow-up to recommendations in respect of each report. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">The Committee continues to ask the Clerk to ensure that sessions are scheduled i</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">nto the Committee’s future programme when it can review, with those responsible for delivery, whether and how the recommendations in its reports have been acted upon. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">For example, in November 2013 it will be reviewing the delivery against recommendations in its </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Catering and Retail Services </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">report (HC 560, 2010-12) and the report </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Visitor Access and Facilities</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt"> (HC13, 2012-13).  The Committee has already scheduled a review</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt"> of recommendations in its more recent report </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">First Weeks at Westminster; induction arrangements of new MPs in 2015</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt"> (HC 193, 2013-14) to take place in May 2014.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Consolas; font-size:10.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Recommendation 36</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.3pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">We recommend that the introductory briefings offered to new committee member</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">s be given more formality, and include a meeting with the chair</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Consolas; font-size:10.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">The Committee has had a </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">high </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">turnover of new members in the last 12 months. </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">All new members to the Committee receive an induction pack with recent minutes and reports. Since April 2013 the Clerk, on the Chair’s behalf, meets all new members to learn more about their specific interests in the House Service and brief them on how the</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt"> Committee works and what topics are currently being discussed. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Innovation</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.3pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">The Administration Committee works very closely with Finance and Services Committee and the Commission</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt"> and often discusses different aspects of the same topic</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">. A memorandum of und</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">erstanding is in the pro</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">c</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">ess of being drafted between the Administration Committee and Finance and Services Committee in order to </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">provide clear guidance to members about the division of responsibilities between these committees. This should also help the C</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">ommittee be more effective</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt"> as any agenda item which is likely to be relevant to both committees can be discussed between the Chairs </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">prior to any meetings </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">in order to determine which committee should discuss it first and what their focus should be. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Sir</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> Alan </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Haselhurst</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">, Chair of the Administration Committee</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">22 October 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-alig